\paragraph{The State}\label{the-state}}

What is a state? \textgreater{} a state is a human community that
(successfully) claims the monopoly of the legitimate use of physical
force within a given territory

Where do states come from?

\textbf{Social contract theory:} \textgreater{} The state rises from the
cumulative experience of a populations\ldots{}

Basically, the need for a leader / social contract arises with size.

